    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Textile having the characteristic that it can be stretched without permanent alteration of size or shape. Examples include yardage or strips of textile material comprising threads or thin strips of rubber or other another elastic substance covered by a woven material.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
